theorem
fixes x :: real and P Q :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. P x = x powr 6 - 16 * x powr 3 + 64"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. Q x = x powr 3 - 8"
and h2 : "Q x \<noteq> 0"
and h3 : "x = 6"
shows  "P x / Q x = 208"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Compute $\frac{x^6-16x^3+64}{x^3-8}$ when $x=6$. The final Answer is 208
 ### Proof
 Note that $\left(x^3-8\right)^2=x^6-16x^3+64$.
 So $\frac{x^6-16x^3+64}{x^3-8}=\frac{\left(x^3-8\right)^2}{x^3-8}=x^3-8$.
 So, the answer is $6^3-8=216-8=\boxed{208}$.
 *)
